Text: You’re the only one who can define what family means to you. Family isn’t one-size-fits-all. But whoever you decide to include in yours, make sure they love you — no matter who you love. 🤍💖🤎🖤❤️🧡💛💚💜💙 #HMPride https://t.co/yx9SjItJ9i

#HMPride #Pride 

https://t.co/9EsX09KoRW

Chosen families are not here to replace your biological family. They exist to expand the definition of family, pulling people together. It's about the rituals you create, the memories you share, and the support you give one another. It's about being there, no matter who you love.

So what is a chosen family? It's a family with non-biological bonds who have intentionally chosen to love and support one another. They are a source of strength within the LGBTQIA+ community and come from the desire to speak openly about shared experiences. #HMPride
You don't have to be born into family, you can choose one. For this year's #HMPride, we celebrate chosen families.

Today is #IDAHOBIT and we’re celebrating families in all their beautiful diversity together with @free_equal
